manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Ideal Solution for Gaming PCs Named after the powerful shield of Greek gods, Aegis symbolizes strength and power. This new addition of DDR4 memory to the AEGIS family of gaming memory is designed for upgraded performance and high stability on the latest PC gaming systems. Give the quality performance boost your gaming rig deserves, no matter the game. Whether it’s FPS, RTS, MOBA, or MMORPG, let AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory be the strength of your gaming arsenal!

Designed for Gamers Available from a standard starting speed of DDR4-2133MHz, give the performance of your system a boost by increasing the amount of transfers per second over the previous generation of DDR3 memory. Upgrade your PC memory speed or capacity with the G.SKILL Aegis DDR4 series for a smoother gaming experience!

Built for Quality Built with the highest quality of hand-selected ICs and rigorously tested on major performance motherboard brands, the AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory is designed for the best compatibility and stability the widest selection of motherboards*. [*Please make sure to check the G.SKILL product webpage for the latest Qualified Vendors List (QVL).]

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Price to performance is unbeatable. Period.
reviews.reviewText: Xmp straight away. No dillying about. Asus ROG B450 board AMD 3600. First build since 08 and I love it. Things are snappy again and games saw 30-40 % improvement over a clarkdale 870 4/8 intel 8gb ram with RX 480.Who cares about systems. Does it work? YES. Is it affordable? YES. Is it 16fb of RAM @3200mhz with XMP enabled? YES. Default to 1.35v from 1.20 @ stock speed ? YES. Should you buy it? If you need 2x8gb kit of ddr4 ram woth room to grow assuming you have 4 dimm slots. YES.Simply unbeatable value for half the price other 16fb kits are going for from the big boys in ram.Only thing I didn’t do was check to see the ram module manufacturer. I’m sure it’s Samsung or some other A grade vendor.Will end up buying another for 32gb before it goes up and ddr5 or some other memory upgrade comes out.Sweet spot for speed and performance for AMD I believe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is perfect!
reviews.reviewText: This is exactly what I ordered and I popped them in and they worked perfect! My PC is running so much better and faster now! I would order these again without hesitation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I paired a set of 2x8gb sticks with an ASUS prime motherboard (cheap $80 mobo) and an i5 9400f. My mobo caps my ram at 2666 but for the gaming I do it works fine. I’ll upgrade the mobo when I do the cpu and I’ll also grab another 16gb to fill in the rest of the ram slots. Again these would be even better if my mobo would allow them to run at full speed lol.Would recommend for someone who does a bit of gaming and doesn’t want to spend out for Corsair or something more expensive. Great for a budget build imho.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Heatsinks are too thin for my taste
reviews.reviewText: If your case has excellent airflow then these thin heatsinks won't have a problem.If you don't, then as long as you're not gaming or pushing them hard then they should be fine. I just prefer thicker heatsinks.The low height and thin heatsink design would be great in a low profile case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Low profile, stable
reviews.reviewText: I already had 16 gig of this same memory in my new Ryzen 3900x we built and I wanted another 16 so I bought the same upgrade kit. The computer is stable and the memory clears the new HUGE heatsync I also upgraded to so something to keep in mind if anyone is thinking of adding a overkill large air cooler to their system. Also the price on these has dropped 20 bucks since I got my sticks so they are very reasonably pricedtoo.

reviews.reviewText: The best price to performance ram product that I found, easy install, works as advertised at 3200 mhz, using it with Ryzan 5 3600 and a B450 Tomahawk Max Motherboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's RAM, it does what RAM does.
reviews.reviewText: I bought the RAM because I got my hands on a SFF PC to run my 7 Days to Die server, it had one stick of 8GB RAM, I hate running single channel RAM. I shopped around a bit and found this, the price was right so I bought it. I have had no crashes or reported error with the RAM, so it's doing what it should and I'm pleased with it.Silly PC still won't brew coffee for me, sigh :)

They're cheap sticks, I had a little trouble getting them seated but that could be partially the motherboard's fault. I purchased because these are low-profile and would clear my Hyper 212 tower cooler. Installed and run at 3200Mhz with Intel XMP on first boot paired with 2 G Skill Trident Z RGB sticks. Would recommend.
